Greuter, 1917
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="E3D72A2E6E34FFC2471FE0E482E6FC49" box="[629,688,991,1017]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="4.[167,200,1775,1797]" captionTargetBox="[202,1183,629,1755]" captionTargetId="figure-172@4.[179,1200,615,1773]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Fig. 3. Gastrotrichs of the Karyakiv ravine pond: A — Chaetonotus (Zonochaeta) bisacer, B — Chaetonotus (Primochaetus) heideri, C — Lepidodermella minor minor, D — Lepidodermella squamata, E — Ichthydium maximum, F — Haltidytes festinans. Scale bars 30 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6455652" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6455652/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="354">fig. 3</figureCitation>
, E)
</heading>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="33F665206E34FFC24589E723826FFA15" pageId="5" pageNumber="354" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph id="7B5336AB6E34FFC24589E7238149FBF8" blockId="5.[174,1232,1048,1097]" pageId="5" pageNumber="354">
Material. 
<specimenCount id="6DEAFD226E34FFC24432E7238186FB9E" box="[344,464,1048,1070]" pageId="5" pageNumber="354" type="generic">3 specimens</specimenCount>
. TL 207–220 µm, al 9–11 µm, pl 63–65 µm, md 8 µm, hw 36–38 µm, nw 33 µm, tw 13,5 µm.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="7B5336AB6E34FFC24589E7518363FB54" blockId="5.[174,1233,1130,1380]" pageId="5" pageNumber="354">
D e s c r i p t i o n. The morphology and the dimensions of the animals collected correspond to the literature data (
<bibRefCitation id="1F7D4B5A6E34FFC24493E7B182F9FB14" author="Schwank, P." box="[505,687,1162,1188]" pageId="5" pageNumber="354" pagination="1 - 252" refId="ref3985" refString="Schwank, P. 1990. Gastrotricha. In: Schwoerbel, J., Zwick, P., eds. Susswasserfauna von Mitteleuropa, Band 3. Gastrotricha und Nemertini. Gustav Fischer Verlag, Stuttgart, Jena, New York, 1 - 252." type="book chapter" year="1990">Schwank, 1990</bibRefCitation>
). Slender body. Head five-lobed with two pairs of cephalic sensory ciliary tufts. Two pairs of dorsal sensory bristles. Furca is short. Both dorsal and ventral sides are naked. Mouth subterminal.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="7B5336AB6E34FFC24589E7D18168FAF4" blockId="5.[174,1233,1130,1380]" pageId="5" pageNumber="354">
D i s t r i b u t i o n a n d e c o l o g y. Reported from Europe: 
<collectingCountry id="03FB763B6E34FFC2461EE7D18444FAB4" box="[884,1042,1258,1284]" name="United Kingdom" pageId="5" pageNumber="354">Great Britain</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="03FB763B6E34FFC24174E7D18422FAB4" box="[1054,1140,1258,1284]" name="Poland" pageId="5" pageNumber="354">Poland</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="03FB763B6E34FFC241EAE7D18083FA94" name="Romania" pageId="5" pageNumber="354">Romania</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="03FB763B6E34FFC24589E6318164FA94" box="[227,306,1290,1316]" name="Russia" pageId="5" pageNumber="354">Russia</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="03FB763B6E34FFC24455E631819FFA94" box="[319,457,1290,1316]" name="Switzerland" pageId="5" pageNumber="354">Switzerland</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry id="03FB763B6E34FFC24762E6318218FA94" box="[520,590,1290,1316]" name="Japan" pageId="5" pageNumber="354">Japan</collectingCountry>
. Usually reported from eutrophic water bodies (
<bibRefCitation id="1F7D4B5A6E34FFC241F9E6318167FAF4" author="Kanneby, T. &amp; Todaro, M. &amp; Jondelius, U." pageId="5" pageNumber="354" refId="ref3769" refString="Kanneby, T., Todaro, M., Jondelius, U. 2009. One new species and records of Ichthydium Ehrenberg, 1830 (Gastrotricha: Chaetonotida) from Sweden with a key to the genus. Zootaxa, 2278, 26 - 16." type="book" year="2009">Kånneby, 2009</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="7B5336AB6E34FFC24589E6718399FAD4" blockId="5.[174,1233,1130,1380]" box="[227,975,1354,1380]" pageId="5" pageNumber="354">
Remarks. This species is reported in 
<collectingCountry id="03FB763B6E34FFC247C8E6718354FAD4" box="[674,770,1354,1380]" name="Ukraine" pageId="5" pageNumber="354">Ukraine</collectingCountry>
for the first time.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="7B5336AB6E34FFC245C4E6B1826FFA15" blockId="5.[174,687,1418,1508]" box="[174,569,1418,1445]" pageId="5" pageNumber="354">
