<taxonomicName id="BCEC4D286E34FFC24469E692827AFA74" authority="Remane, 1936" authorityName="Remane" authorityYear="1936" box="[259,556,1449,1476]" family="Dasydytidae" genus="Haltidytes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chaetonotida" pageId="5" pageNumber="354" phylum="Gastrotricha" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="4998EAB96E34FFC24469E69281D6FA74" bold="true" box="[259,384,1449,1476]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="354">Haltidytes</emphasis>
Remane, 1936
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="7B5336AB6E34FFC245C4E6F282F9FA54" blockId="5.[174,687,1418,1508]" box="[174,687,1481,1508]" pageId="5" pageNumber="354">
<taxonomicName id="BCEC4D286E34FFC245C4E6F28269FA54" authority="(Voigt, 1909)" baseAuthorityName="Voigt" baseAuthorityYear="1909" box="[174,575,1481,1508]" family="Dasydytidae" genus="Haltidytes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chaetonotida" pageId="5" pageNumber="354" phylum="Gastrotricha" rank="species" species="festinans">
<emphasis id="4998EAB96E34FFC245C4E6F281CAFA53" bold="true" box="[174,412,1481,1508]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="354">Haltidytes festinans</emphasis>
(Voigt, 1909)
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="E3D72A2E6E34FFC24724E6F182DFFA54" box="[590,649,1482,1508]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="4.[167,200,1775,1797]" captionTargetBox="[202,1183,629,1755]" captionTargetId="figure-172@4.[179,1200,615,1773]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Fig. 3. Gastrotrichs of the Karyakiv ravine pond: A — Chaetonotus (Zonochaeta) bisacer, B — Chaetonotus (Primochaetus) heideri, C — Lepidodermella minor minor, D — Lepidodermella squamata, E — Ichthydium maximum, F — Haltidytes festinans. Scale bars 30 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6455652" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6455652/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="354">fig. 3</figureCitation>
, F)
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="7B5336AB6E34FFC24589E538841DF9A8" blockId="5.[227,1099,1539,1561]" box="[227,1099,1539,1561]" pageId="5" pageNumber="354">
Material. 
<specimenCount id="6DEAFD226E34FFC24438E5388197F9A9" box="[338,449,1539,1561]" pageId="5" pageNumber="354" type="generic">1 specimen</specimenCount>
. TL 126 µm, pL 37 µm, md 7.8 µm, hw 45 µm, nw 22 µm, tw 20 µm.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="7B5336AB6E34FFC24589E501843DF904" blockId="5.[174,1233,1594,1844]" pageId="5" pageNumber="354">
D e s c r i p t i o n. The morphology and the dimensions of the animal collected correspond to the literature data (
<bibRefCitation id="1F7D4B5A6E34FFC244D3E5618225F9C4" author="Schwank, P." box="[441,627,1626,1652]" pageId="5" pageNumber="354" pagination="1 - 252" refId="ref3985" refString="Schwank, P. 1990. Gastrotricha. In: Schwoerbel, J., Zwick, P., eds. Susswasserfauna von Mitteleuropa, Band 3. Gastrotricha und Nemertini. Gustav Fischer Verlag, Stuttgart, Jena, New York, 1 - 252." type="book chapter" year="1990">Schwank, 1990</bibRefCitation>
). Stocky body. Triangular head. Cephalic ciliature composed by 3 paired tufts. Dorsal side has 5 pairs of long crossing spines. Ventrally, beyond the trunk end, saltatorial and caudal spines do not cross. Mouth terminal.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="7B5336AB6E34FFC24589E5818195F8A4" blockId="5.[174,1233,1594,1844]" pageId="5" pageNumber="354">
Distribution and ecology. Usually reported from mesosaprobic water bodies (
<bibRefCitation id="1F7D4B5A6E34FFC24464E5E18193F945" author="Sladecek, V." box="[270,453,1754,1781]" pageId="5" pageNumber="354" refId="ref4033" refString="Sladecek, V. 1976. Indicator value of freshwater Gastrotricha. Acta hydrochim. hydrobiol., 4" type="book" year="1976">Sladeček, 1976</bibRefCitation>
). Reported from 
<collectingCountry id="03FB763B6E34FFC247F6E5E182B9F944" box="[668,751,1754,1780]" name="Poland" pageId="5" pageNumber="354">Poland</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry id="03FB763B6E34FFC24659E5E1832EF944" box="[819,888,1754,1780]" name="Brazil" pageId="5" pageNumber="354">Brazil</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="1F7D4B5A6E34FFC246E1E5E18437F944" author="Kisielewski, J." box="[907,1121,1754,1780]" pageId="5" pageNumber="354" pagination="1 - 168" refId="ref3851" refString="Kisielewski, J. 1991. Inland-water Gastrotricha from Brazil. Annales Zoologici Warszawa, 43 (2), 1 - 168." type="journal article" year="1991">Kisielewski, 1991</bibRefCitation>
). Typical semiplanktonic species.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="7B5336AB6E34FFC24589E4218399F884" blockId="5.[174,1233,1594,1844]" box="[227,975,1818,1844]" pageId="5" pageNumber="354">
Remarks. This species is reported in 
<collectingCountry id="03FB763B6E34FFC247C8E4218354F884" box="[674,770,1818,1844]" name="Ukraine" pageId="5" pageNumber="354">Ukraine</collectingCountry>
for the first time.
</paragraph>
